                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.736,
                                "byte_start": 104448,
                                "byte_stop": 139452,
                                "text": "I have the opinion of the Court this morning in case 10-8145, Juan Smith versus Burl Cain."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 8.736,
                                "stop": 13.408,
                                "byte_start": 139452,
                                "byte_stop": 158156,
                                "text": "Juan Smith was convicted of murdering five people during an armed robbery."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 13.408,
                                "stop": 18.176,
                                "byte_start": 158156,
                                "byte_stop": 177173,
                                "text": "At Smith\u0027s trial, a single eyewitness linked Smith to the crime."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.176,
                                "stop": 22.81,
                                "byte_start": 177173,
                                "byte_stop": 195772,
                                "text": "No other witnesses and no physical evidence implicated Smith."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 22.81,
                                "stop": 27.434,
                                "byte_start": 195772,
                                "byte_stop": 214267,
                                "text": "Smith later obtained files from the police investigation of the crime."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.434,
                                "stop": 41.702,
                                "byte_start": 214267,
                                "byte_stop": 271318,
                                "text": "Those files showed that the key eyewitness had told the police among other things that he \u201ccould not ID anyone because he could not see their faces\u201d and that he \u201cwould not know them if he saw them.\u0022"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 41.702,
                                "stop": 46.851,
                                "byte_start": 271318,
                                "byte_stop": 291903,
                                "text": "The witness nonetheless had confidently identified Smith in Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.851,
                                "stop": 51.53,
                                "byte_start": 291903,
                                "byte_stop": 310606,
                                "text": "In 1963, we decided a case called Brady versus Maryland."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.53,
                                "stop": 63.548,
                                "byte_start": 310606,
                                "byte_stop": 358672,
                                "text": "In that case, we explained that prosecutors may not withhold from criminal defendants evidence that is favorable to the defence and material to determining the defendant\u0027s guilt or innocence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 63.548,
                                "stop": 73.342,
                                "byte_start": 358672,
                                "byte_stop": 397855,
                                "text": "The State in this case acknowledges as it must that the witness\u0027 statements were not given to Smith and that those statements were helpful to him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 73.342,
                                "stop": 77.854,
                                "byte_start": 397855,
                                "byte_stop": 415932,
                                "text": "The only question, therefore, is whether the statements were material."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.854,
                                "stop": 88.986,
                                "byte_start": 415932,
                                "byte_stop": 460445,
                                "text": "We have said that statements are material if there is a \u201creasonable probability\u0027 that the result of the trial would have been different had the evidence been disclosed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.986,
                                "stop": 105.046,
                                "byte_start": 460445,
                                "byte_stop": 524706,
                                "text": "Now, when the only evidence linking a defendant to a crime is an identification by a single eyewitness and that witness had previously told the police that he could not ID anyone because he could not see their faces, it\u0027s pretty clear that the withheld evidence is material."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.046,
                                "stop": 124.003,
                                "byte_start": 524706,
                                "byte_stop": 600461,
                                "text": "The State contends that the jury might have disregarded Smith\u0027s undisclosed statements because the witness had also -- the statements that weren\u0027t disclosed to Smith because the witness had also told police shortly after the crime that he could make an identification of one of the shooters."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.003,
                                "stop": 158.918,
                                "byte_start": 600461,
                                "byte_stop": 740164,
                                "text": "According to the State, the witness\u0027 statement that he could not see the perpetrators\u0027 faces meant that he could not see the faces of perpetrators other than the one he could identify and the State claims that the witness\u0027 later statement that he would not know the perpetrators if he saw them can be explained by his legitimate fear of possible retaliation, but all that only leaves as to speculate about which of the witness\u0027 contradictory statements the jury would have believed, the statements in which the witness said he could identify Smith or those in which he said he could not."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.918,
                                "stop": 171.254,
                                "byte_start": 740164,
                                "byte_stop": 789483,
                                "text": "Because there is a reasonable probability that the jury would have believed the witness\u0027 statements that he could not identify Smith, we can have no confidence in Smith\u0027s conviction."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 171.254,
                                "stop": 177.098,
                                "byte_start": 789483,
                                "byte_stop": 812889,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Orleans Parish Criminal District Court of Louisiana is accordingly reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.098,
                                "stop": 180.141,
                                "byte_start": 812889,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
